Cheap mé go raibh An í seo do bheatha aisteach go leor go mbeidh daoine ag teacht ar seoltaí as Gaeilge agus ag seol an sórt sin ráiméise. B’fhéidir gur sheol siad na céadta dóibh. Dochreidte ach ansin ar maidin léigh mé an tuairisc seo i Metro Herald –

Warning over Irish spam mail
Irish computer users have been warned to be alert to the latest attack by cybercriminals: spam as Gaeilge. Security firm ESET Ireland said spam is becoming increasingly targeted, prompting ever-industrious spammers to construct emails in Irish which they hope will be more convincing.


